11
00:01:29,149 --> 00:01:32,278
It does.

12
00:01:33,750 --> 00:01:40,006
In the olden days people used to
store ice by encasing it in sawdust.

13
00:01:41,347 --> 00:01:44,143
Yea, but what do you mean,
what are you trying to say.

14
00:01:44,177 --> 00:01:47,095
This mountain, it's like a giant icebox.

15
00:01:47,757 --> 00:01:50,302
For storing, what?

16
00:01:50,367 --> 00:01:54,540
- Drill deeper and you will see.

17
00:01:55,231 --> 00:01:57,233
Well, I am..
They're drilling as we speak

18
00:02:06,755 --> 00:02:09,884
- Make sure everyone has one of these.
- What are these?

19
00:02:11,057 --> 00:02:13,685
It's the new safety instructions.

20
00:02:13,765 --> 00:02:15,675
Wash behind the ears.

21
00:02:15,775 --> 00:02:18,069
This is funny shit!

22
00:02:18,104 --> 00:02:20,381
Watch your mouth!

23
00:02:20,416 --> 00:02:23,101
It's Christmas time.

24
00:02:23,137 --> 00:02:25,788
So, let's act like it.

25
00:02:26,872 --> 00:02:30,002
KORVATUNTURI mountain drill site

26
00:02:32,507 --> 00:02:35,354
Hey, someone's coming.

27
00:02:35,389 --> 00:02:38,518
Mr. Green, I think we found something.

28
00:02:45,600 --> 00:02:48,396
Sample number 98.

29
00:02:48,431 --> 00:02:51,560
I think you were right.

30
00:03:06,772 --> 00:03:11,986
Always believe, always.

31
00:03:30,887 --> 00:03:34,016
Gentlemen, listen up.

32
00:03:34,584 --> 00:03:37,714
My dream, since my early childhood

33
00:03:37,883 --> 00:03:42,871
Is about.. to come true.

34
00:03:51,840 --> 00:03:54,970
I can proudly say,

35
00:03:56,451 --> 00:04:00,624
That we are standing on the sacred grave..

36
00:04:00,828 --> 00:04:05,313
Biggest burial mound in the world.

37
00:04:06,460 --> 00:04:08,595
Something's been buried here.

38
00:04:08,630 --> 00:04:13,114
This remarkable place puts
even the pyramids to shame.

39
00:04:13,762 --> 00:04:20,019
It took the Saami-People of Lapland
centuries to build this mound,

40
00:04:21,564 --> 00:04:25,735
You have 24 days to open it.

41
00:04:26,361 --> 00:04:31,576
Roll up the sleeves, prepare the dynamite,
do what you do best!

42
00:04:32,411 --> 00:04:35,373
They're going to blow up this mountain.

43
00:04:35,408 --> 00:04:39,544
We have a grave to rob.

44
00:04:41,905 --> 00:04:43,785
Juuso!

45
00:04:47,584 --> 00:04:50,713
Juuso! Wait!

46
00:04:54,093 --> 00:04:57,223
Santa's been buried.

47
00:05:09,274 --> 00:05:12,221
Juuso! Is Santa Claus dead?

48
00:05:12,257 --> 00:05:15,385
Idiot, you still believe in Santa Claus?

49
00:05:15,562 --> 00:05:19,166
You're such a little kid. Come on already.

50
00:05:20,453 --> 00:05:23,582
- So they've lied to us this whole time.
- At least to you.

51
00:05:24,062 --> 00:05:25,988
What Santa came to our home then?

52
00:05:26,022 --> 00:05:29,152
Piiparinen, haven't you realized that?

53
00:05:29,819 --> 00:05:32,949
Piiparinen? Do you think Dad knows?

54
00:05:33,032 --> 00:05:35,430
Your dad pays him for it.

55
00:05:35,465 --> 00:05:37,794
Don't you understand, kid?

56
00:05:37,830 --> 00:05:40,958
The whole Santa business is a fraud.

57
00:06:14,753 --> 00:06:17,882
The Truth About Santa Claus.

58
00:06:19,342 --> 00:06:22,471
First Santa Claus.

59
00:06:29,438 --> 00:06:32,568
Have you been naughty?

60
00:06:43,957 --> 00:06:47,086
Santa walks barefoot in the snow.

61
00:07:14,288 --> 00:07:17,418
Santa making Christmas-Stew.

62
00:07:48,083 --> 00:07:51,211
1 day before Christmas

63
00:09:21,394 --> 00:09:24,483
Pietari!

64
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:30,000
Upcoming jump scare (Minor)
Wake up! Wake up, son!

65
00:09:45,709 --> 00:09:48,838
